<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2922] ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException when specifying no name</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2922</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When parsing a encoded string without a name in the constructor of ConditionalPermissionInfoImpl you get a ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException. If I&apos;m correct the syntax in the specification is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;policy ::= access &apos;&lt;/p&gt;
{&apos; conditions permissions&apos;}
&lt;p&gt;&apos; name?&lt;br/&gt;
access ::= &apos;ALLOW&apos; | &apos;DENY&apos; // case insensitive&lt;br/&gt;
name ::= quoted-string&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;doesn&apos;t that make the name optional?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
