                            <comment id="13021580" author="karlpauls" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2011 13:34:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, i guess you&apos;re right. Looks like a bug. I&apos;ll try to get to it soon. Thanks for reporting. Workaround for now is to just always give a name right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13026987" author="slimmy" created="Fri, 29 Apr 2011 14:25:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also it says here that it is case insensitive but the parser obviously only parses uppercase ALLOW or DENY statements. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13102529" author="karlpauls" created="Mon, 12 Sep 2011 10:13:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I commited a fix for this. If you want to test it, you&apos;d need to work with framework and framework.security trunk for now. Please close this issue if it work for you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
